Vug: cavity inside rock
Polymorphism: different crystal structures based on temperature and pressure

#Color
Idiochromatic: main elements
Allochromatic: trace elements
Sulfur: yellow
Chromium: red/green
Manganese: purple
Iron: red/brown
Cobalt: blue
Nickel: green
Copper: green/blue

#Cleavage: planes mineral breaks along
#Streak: color of powder trail

#Luster: reflection of light
Asterism: 4/6/8-rayed star
Aventurescence: glitter-like reflection
Chatoyancy: bands of reflection (Tiger's eye)
Iridescence: rainbow colors (Opal)
Photochromism: change of color when exposed to light
- Tenebrescence: darkening when exposed to light
--
Adamantine: diamond
Dull: earth-like
Greasy: fat-like
Metallic: shiny
Vitreous: glass-like
Pearly
Resinous
Silky

#Mohs scale: hardness
1: Talc, softest
2: Gypsum
3: Calcite, not scratched by fingernail
4: Fluorite
5: Apatite
6: Orthoclase, not scratched by knife or glass
7: Quartz
8: Topaz
9: Corundum
10: Diamond, hardest

#Crystal habit: external crystal shape
rounded (hematite, goethite)
- Botryoidal: bubble-like, hemispherical
- Reniform: kidney-like, lobed
- Colloform: concentric layers (agate, malachite)
symmetrical
- Prismatic: elongated polygonal (quartz, beryl)
- Tetrahedral
- Cubic (halite)
- Octahedral: square bipyramid (spinel)
- Dodecahedral (garnet)
- Rhombohedral: distorted cubic
- Scalenohedral: distorted octahedral
branched (copper)
- Arborescent- tree-like, branching
- Dendritic: root-like, branching
aggregate
- Acicular: needle-like, slender (stibnite)
- Plumose: feather-like, fine
--
- Hopper: hollowed-out lattice
- Lenticular: plate-like, thin
- Tabular: flat plates
--
- Druse: coating of surface (quartz)
- Stalactite: hanging from cave ceiling (calcite)
- Stalagmite: rising from cave floor (calcite)

#Native
Carbon
- Graphite: hexagonal, soft, black, metallic
- Diamond: cubic, octahedral, hard, transparent
Sulfur: orthorhombic, resinous, soft, yellow color
Copper
Silver
Gold

#Oxide
Corundum = Al2O3: trigonal, hard, allochromatic, translucent, no cleavage, vitreous
- Ruby: red by chromium
- Sapphire: blue by iron + titanium
Rutile = TiO2: tetragonal, acicular, brown color, white pigment
- Brookite: orthorhombic, tabular, translucent
Hematite = Fe2O3: trigonal, botryoidal, red pigment, metallic
Cassiterite = SnO2: tetragonal, metallic

#Carbonate (CO3): transparent to translucent, vitreous
Magnesite = MgCO3: trigonal
Calcite = CaCO3: trigonal, various habits, colorless to white, vitreous to pearly
Aragonite = CaCO3: orthorhombic, acicular and prismatic
Rhodochrosite = MnCO3: trigonal, rhombohedral or scelanohedral, pink color, white streak
Siderite = FeCO3: trigonal, tabular
Malachite = CuCO3(OH)2: monoclinic, botryoidal, green pigment
Azurite = Cu3(CO3)2(OH)2: monoclinic, blue pigment
Smithsonite = ZnCO3: trigonal, botryoidal, allochromatic
Cerussite = PbCO3: orthorhombic

#Silicate: transparent to translucent, no cleavage, vitreous

==Cyclosilicate: rings
Beryl = (BeO)3(Al2O3)(SiO2)6: hexagonal, prismatic, hard, allochromatic
- Emerald: green by chromium
- Aquamarine: blue-green by iron
Tourmaline: trigonal, prismatic, hard, allochromatic, with boron + aluminium
- Elbaite: with lithium + sodium
- Dravite: with sodium + magnesium
- Schorl: with iron

==Nesosilicate: isolated tetrahedra
Phenakite = Be2SiO4: trigonal
Willemite = Zn2SiO4: trigonal, UV fluorescent
Olivine/Peridot = (Mg,Fe)2SiO4: orthorhombic, yellow-green
Zircon = ZrSiO4: tetragonal, hard, allochromatic
=Garnets: X3Y2(SiO4)3, cubic, dodecahedral
Spessartine - Mn3Al2(SiO4)3: orange
Almandine - Fe3Al2(SiO4)3 : purple

==Sorosilicate: double tetrahedra
Epidote: monoclinic, prismatic, greenish
Zoisite: orthorhombic, prismatic
- Tanzanite: violet by vanadium
Vesuvianite/Idocrase: tetragonal, prismatic, green or brown
Hemimorphite: orthorhombic, prismatic or reniform, white or bluish, zinc
Allanite: monoclinic, prismatic, black, rare earths

==Inosilicate: chain
=Pyroxene (XYZ2O6)
Jadeite = NaAlSi2O6: monoclinic, green color, pearly
Diopside = MgCaSi2O6: monoclinic, green to white

==Tectosilicate: 3D framework
Coesite = SiO2: monoclinic, high pressure, impact event
Tridymite = SiO2: orthorhombic or hexagonal, tabular, high temperature
Cristobalite = SiO2: tetragonal, very high temperature
=Quartz = SiO2: trigonal or hexagonal, prismatic or botryoidal, allochromatic, conchoidal fracture, sharp edges
- Amethyst: purple by iron
- Citrine: yellow by iron
- Jasper: red by iron, opaque
--Chalcedony
- Agate: banded
- Onyx: parallel bands
- Carnelian: brown
=Feldspar: aluminium silicate
Alkali
- Orthoclase: KAlSi3O8, monoclinic, white streak
- Microcline: KAlSi3O8, triclinic, white streak
Plagioclase
- Albite: NaAlSi3O8, triclinic, white streak
- Anorthite: CaAl2Si2O8, triclinic, white streak

=Phyllosilicate: sheet-like layers
Clay
- Kaolinite: white
Mica
- Muscovite: flakes

#Sulfate (SO4): orthorhombic, transparent to translucent, vitreous
Anhydrite = CaSO4: pearly to greasy
Celestine = SrSO4
Baryte = BaSO4: tabular, colorless to white
Anglesite = PbSO4

#Hydroxide
Gibbsite = Al(OH)3: monoclinic, botryoidal
Goethite = FeO(OH): orthorhombic, acicular or botryoidal, brown pigment, rust component
=Silicate
Dioptase = CuSiO2(OH)2: trigonal, blue-green
=Sulfate
Brochantite = Cu4SO4(OH)6: monoclinic, acicular, green color, translucent

#Spinels (XY2O4): cubic, octahedral
Spinel = MgAl2O4: hard, transparent to translucent, allochromatic, vitreous
Magnetite = FeFe2O4: metallic

#Chromate
Chromite - FeCr2O4: cubic
Crocoite - PbCrO4: monoclinic, acicular, orange pigment, toxic
#Molybdate
Wulfenite - PbMoO4: tetragonal, tabular, yellow color, resinous
#Tungstate
Scheelite - CaWO4: tetragonal, UV fluorescent
Wolframite - (Fe,Mn)WO4: monoclinic, tabular to prismatic, black

#Sulfide: opaque
Pyrite = FeS2: face-centered cubic, cubic, golden color, metallic, black streak
Marcasite = FeS2: orthorhombic, tabular or reniform, silver to bronze color, metallic
Arsenopyrite = FeAsS: monoclinic, metallic, found with gold
Millerite = NiS: trigonal, acicular
Covellite = CuS: hexagonal, soft, dark blue
Chalcocite = Cu2S: monoclinic
Chalcopyrite = CuFeS2: tetragonal, tetrahedral, golden color, metallic, black streak
Sphalerite = (Zn,Fe)S: face-centered cubic, tetrahedral, resinous
Realgar = As4S4: monoclinic, prismatic, soft, red pigment, resinous, toxic
Orpiment = As2S3: monoclinic, soft, yellow pigment, resinous, toxic
Molybdenite = MoS2: soft, black, metallic, similar to graphite
Acanthite = Ag2S: monoclinic, metallic
Stibnite = Sb2S3: orthorhombic, acicular, metallic, soft
Cinnabar = HgS: trigonal, soft, red pigment, toxic
Galena = PbS: cubic, octahedral, metallic, trace silver

#Halide: transparent to translucent, vitreous
Halite = NaCl: cubic, soft
Sylvite = KCl: cubic, soft
Fluorite = CaF2: cubic, allochromatic, UV fluorescent, white streak
Calomel = Hg2Cl2: tetragonal, soft, toxic

#Hydrate (H2O)
Opal - SiO2: iridescent

Obsidian: volcanic glass, conchoidal fracture, sharp edges, black color
